In Norse Mythology, Bifrost Bridge is the bridge leading from the realm of the mortals (Midgrd) to the realm of the gods (Asgrd).
The bridge itself is the rainbow and its guardian is the god Heimdall.
The bridge is destroyed at the end of the world (Ragnarok) and was built by the gods.
